name: esterification of soybean oil | glycerine | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10006/documentation

This dataset represents the production of soybean methyl ester, respectively glycerine, from crude soybean oil. Density of methyl ester = 0.88 kg/l

From reception of raw materials at the factory gate through esterification of crude soybean oil.

The dataset includes intermediate storage of the oil and products. System boundary is at the esterification plant.
category: C:Manufacturing/19:Manufacture of coke and refined petroleum products/192:Manufacture of refined petroleum products/1920:Manufacture of refined petroleum products

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data from 1996 to 2003, current technology for large scale biodiesel plants worldwide
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from different plants worldwide (incl. literature data)
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Typical vegetable oil esterification plant designed for the production of methyl ester (for use in the vehicle fuels market), global context. Base-catalyzed transesterification.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Cross-checking of various literature sources from 1998 to 2006

exchanges.description:
EcoSpold01Location=RER
Literature, environmental report
Calculated based on literature (Sheenhan, J., 18, An Overview of Biodiesel and Petroleum Diesel Life Cycles; Omni Tech International, 2010, Life Cycle Impact of Soybean Production and Soy Industrial Products), (Vionnet, S., Quantis Water Database - Technical Report, 2012). The process starts when refined soybean oil enters the plant. It includes the processes: prepurification, deacidification, transesterification, destilation, etc. It is assumed that 95% of water use is allocated to cooling water and 5% of water is allocated as process water.
